snippet: Fui a urgencias el jueves 22/02 trasladada en ambulancia por un dolor en la pierna izquierda, por una ciática  y al llegar al hospital lo primero que dijeron que porque me habían llevado allí si ellos tenían las ambulancias paradas porque no tenían camas, y así tuve que quedarme en un box de urgencias a pasar la noche, sin dormir por todo el ruido y la incomodidad, sin baño, sin poderse quedar un acompañante, en fin una vergüenza y al otro día luego de hacerme una epidural y una radiofrecuencia me mandaron a casa una hora después de ese proceso tan doloroso sin haberme dejado en la REA por lo menos un tiempo prudente para darme el alta. Un trato inhumano por lo menos del Dr de urgencias quien fue que decidió darme el alta. Soy cliente de Sanitas desde hace más de 7 años, y este trato no se lo merece nadie

extracted_snippet.translated: I went to the emergency room on Thursday 02/22, transported by ambulance due to pain in my left leg, due to sciatica, and when I arrived at the hospital the first thing they said was that why had they taken me there if they had the ambulances stopped because they didn't have beds, and so on. I had to stay in an emergency room to spend the night, without sleeping because of all the noise and discomfort, without a bathroom, without being able to have a companion, in short a shame and the next day after having an epidural and a radiofrequency they sent me I went home an hour after that painful process without having left me in the REA for at least a reasonable amount of time to discharge myself. Inhumane treatment at least from the emergency doctor who decided to discharge me. I have been a Sanitas customer for more than 7 years, and no one deserves this treatment.

snippet:
Mi experiencia fue nefasta acudí 2 años atrás para una operación de nariz tanto estética como por salud, de la cual me salió horrible, la nariz se me quedo mas torcida, las fosas nasales desiguales y el tabique también torcido de tal manera que se veía a simple vista, a eso que vuelvo para las revisiones y efectivamente el médico (Doctor Antonio Lara Peinado ) me dice que han salido muchas cosas mal y que me van a tener que volver a operar, asi que pasado un año me volví a someter a otra cirugía para reparar los fallos que habían cometido… , un año mas tarde y después de dos cirugías mi nariz se sigue viendo torcida la punta con desniveles y en el tabique con bolas de cartílagos a la que vuelvo a la clínica para la revisión y adivinen que me dice? Que me tienen que volver a operar para arreglarlo otra vez .

TENGAN MUCHO CUIDADOO CON QUIEN SE OPEREN

My experience was disastrous. I went 2 years ago for a nose operation, both cosmetic and for health reasons, which turned out horribly, my nose became more crooked, my nostrils were uneven and my septum was also twisted in such a way that it looked like At first glance, I return for the check-ups and indeed the doctor (Doctor Antonio Lara Peinado) tells me that many things have gone wrong and that they are going to have to operate again, so after a year I underwent another one. surgery to repair the mistakes they had made..., a year later and after two surgeries my nose still looks crooked at the tip with unevenness and in the septum with balls of cartilage to which I return to the clinic for the check-up and guess what? tells me? They have to operate on me again to fix it again.
BUT ARE YOU REALLY AWARE THAT IN ADDITION TO PAYING €5,000 FOR SOMETHING THAT HAD TO GO WELL FROM THE FIRST MOMENT, I HAVE TO UNDERGO 3 OPERATIONS????
2 YEARS CONTINUED TO ANESTHESIA TO PAINFUL RECOVERIES TO SEEING MY NOSE CONSTANTLY WRONG WITH MY NOSE... WHAT A REAL SHAME A LOT OF PRIVATE, PRIVATE AND THEN UNQUALIFIED PEOPLE IN THE FIELD
BE VERY CAREFUL WITH WHOM YOU OPERATE WITH
I WILL TAKE LEGAL MEASURES…
THIS IS A SHAME

snippet: Aboné 2.500€ por una cirugía de mohs en la oreja y me indicaron que en ese pago se incluía cualquier consulta que tuviese relación con la intervención. Me operé y a la semana acudí a que me realizasen las curas. El cirujano me comentó que acudiese al terminar la cura a la consulta del otorrino del mismo hospital, ya que quería asegurarse de que no había restos obstruyendo el conducto auditivo. Fui a dicha consulta, le comenté la situación a las recepcionistas (haciéndoles hincapié en que no tenia seguro y que la operación la había pagado por mi cuenta)y me dijeron que no había problema y el otorrino tenia un hueco para verme. Pasé a la consulta y me dijo que no tenia nada en el oido (fueron 30 segundos de consulta) y al salir la chica de recepción me llama y me dice que no me puedo ir sin abonar la consulta, que son 120€. Le explico la situación y que cuando pague la operación me aseguraron que todo lo que guardase relación con la misma estaba incluido y me dijo que no. Así que tuve que abonar 120€ a pesar de lo que me dijeron el primer dia y ademas de no haberme avisado la recepcionista previamente de lo que tendria que abonar. Me siento robado y estafado

extracted_snippet.translated: I paid €2,500 for Mohs surgery on my ear and they told me that this payment included any consultation related to the intervention. I had surgery and a week later I went to have the treatments performed. The surgeon told me to go to the ENT office at the same hospital after the treatment was finished, since he wanted to make sure that there was no debris obstructing the ear canal. I went to that consultation, I mentioned the situation to the receptionists (emphasizing that I did not have insurance and that I had paid for the operation on my own) and they told me that there was no problem and the ENT doctor had a time to see me. I went to the consultation and she told me that I had nothing in my ear (it was a 30 second consultation) and when I left the girl at the reception called me and told me that I couldn't leave without paying for the consultation, which was €120. I explained the situation to him and that when I paid for the operation they assured me that everything related to it was included and he told me no. So I had to pay €120 despite what they told me on the first day and in addition to the fact that the receptionist had not notified me in advance of what I would have to pay. I feel robbed and cheated

snippet:
El día 30 de enero tuve consulta con Dermatología y me atendió la doctora Natalia del Olmo. Acudí a consulta porque me apareció un bultito en la cara con una pequeña mancha y me diagnosticó queratosis seborreica. Me explicó que me lo podía disimular en consulta quemando el tejido con nitrógeno (crioterapia) allí mismo, pero que no me iba a desaparecer al 100%.

Casi 15 días después, ya no tengo absolutamente NADA, mi piel ha quedado perfecta. Muchas gracias a la doctora Natalia por su profesionalidad y su buen trato. Me ha quitado un gran complejo que tenía y que me estaba atormentando.

extracted_snippet.translated:
On January 30, I had a consultation with Dermatology and Dr. Natalia del Olmo saw me. I went to the consultation because a lump appeared on my face with a small spot and I was diagnosed with seborrheic keratosis. He explained to me that I could hide it in the office by burning the tissue with nitrogen (cryotherapy) right there, but that it was not going to disappear 100%.

Almost 15 days later, I have absolutely NOTHING, my skin is perfect. Many thanks to Dr. Natalia for her professionalism and good treatment. It has removed a big complex that I had and that was tormenting me.
response.snippet:

Gracias por dedicarnos tiempo y comunicarnos tu opinión, la cual trasladaremos al equipo médico.
Que tengas un buen día.
